(49, 1396, 'en', 'description', '<p><strong>Electrox designs and builds systems for laser marking etching and engraving applications. Our systems are installed and supported around the world for use in many key industries, including automotive, medical, general engineering and promotional giftware.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The laser technology Electrox designs and manufactures - for <u>laser marking</u>, <u>laser etching</u> and <u>laser engraving</u> applications - is clean and safe, providing indelible, high quality marks in any configuration, rapidly and cost-effectively.&nbsp; In addition, Electrox laser systems are very user-friendly,&nbsp;flexible and&nbsp;adaptable to&nbsp; almost any application you may have.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our extensive product range includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Laser Marking, Etching &amp; Engraving Systems</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electrox laser marking, etching and engraving systems utilise a range of technologies including Fibre, CO2 and Ultra Violet, to permanently&nbsp;mark substances including metals, glass, plastic,&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.6em;">wood, ceramics and many other </span><u style="line-height: 1.6em;">&lsquo;exotic&rsquo; materials</u><span style="line-height: 1.6em;"> such as graphite</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To compare the different Laser Marking/Etching/Engraving Systems available from Electrox, download our <a href="http://www.electrox.com/sales-&amp;-service/brochure-downloads">product range brochure</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Laser Workstations for Marking, Etching and Engraving</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to its core range of high-powered lasers, Electrox offers a range of workstations&nbsp;with either a table/bench-mounted or free-standing format. This enables&nbsp; Electrox to supply both standalone and turnkey laser marking, etching and engraving solutions.&nbsp; All Electrox workstations are Class&nbsp;I enclosures, certified against laser emissions and are fully interlocked to ensure maximum safety.</p>\r\n'),
