(249, 1416, 'en', 'description', '<p>For most bright steels, a surface colour change can be achieved by annealing using laser-marking equipment. Enabled by precision-controlling the heat output, the laser marker is able to produce a highly legible mark in varying colours on the surface being marked, <em>without employing additives.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electrox recommends the following laser marking equipment for high-quality marking by annealing:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.electrox.com/products/raptor-fibre-laser">Raptor Fibre&nbsp;Laser Marker</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.electrox.com/products/scorpion-rapide-fibre-laser">Scorpion Fibre Laser Marker</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://electrox.oxygen-test.co.uk/products/razor-co2-laser">Razor CO2 Laser Marker</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br />\r\nExamples of&nbsp;Annealing in industry</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://electrox.oxygen-test.co.uk/applications/machine-cutting-tools">Milling Cutter (Machine Cutting Tools)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://electrox.oxygen-test.co.uk/applications/medical">Spine Clamp (Medical)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://electrox.oxygen-test.co.uk/applications/medical">Pill Punch (Medical)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://electrox.oxygen-test.co.uk/applications/medical">Medical Instruments (Medical)</a></p>\r\n'),
