(319, 1423, 'en', 'description', '<p>Ablation involves creating marks on anodised, plated or painted products by using a laser marking system to remove the top layer, which exposes the base material in a contrasting colour. By removing an opaque layer from a substrate the creation of graphics for back-lit, day/night products and light show projection devices is enabled.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Marking materials using surface ablation can easily be&nbsp;achieved with the following laser marking&nbsp;equipment from Electrox:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.electrox.com/products/raptor-fibre-laser">Raptor Fibre&nbsp;Laser Marker</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.electrox.com/products/scorpion-rapide-fibre-laser">Scorpion Enhanced&nbsp;Fibre Laser Marker</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://electrox.oxygen-test.co.uk/products/razor-co2-laser">Razor CO2 Laser Marker</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Examples of surface ablation in industry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Day/Night&nbsp;<a href="http://www.electrox.com/applications/automotive">Backlit Switches (Automotive)</a></p>\r\n'),
