(560, 1445, 'en', 'mark_type', 'Vector'),
(561, 1440, 'en', 'material_description', 'Translucent moulded plastic'),
(562, 1440, 'en', 'process_description', 'The plastic is spray coated with multiple layers of colour and the laser marking equipment is then used to carefully remove the individual layers. This leaves an indelible mark.\r\n\r\nThis process is called surface ablation and involves vaporising the painted layers using a suitable laser. It results in an image that can be seen during the day and is illuminated from the rear at night. This laser marking process can produce very fine detail and does not use any harmful inks or chemicals that, conventionally, are associated with this process. \r\n'),
(563, 1445, 'en', 'material_description', 'Plastic'),
(564, 1445, 'en', 'process_description', 'Laser marking here is achieved by creating a program to vector steer the laser beam. This achieves controlled melting of the plastic to produce the desired image and the contrast colour change required.\r\nConventional fuse box covers have their ratings and positional information either moulded or printed onto the materials surface. By changing the process used to laser marking, the need for multiple moulds or mould inserts is removed and the set-up time required for other methods is dramatically reduced. \r\n'),
(565, 1446, 'en', 'image', ''),
(566, 1446, 'en', 'status', 'Live'),
(567, 1446, 'en', 'material_description', 'ABS PC plastic'),
(568, 1446, 'en', 'marked', 'Washing Machine Control Panel'),
(569, 1446, 'en', 'process_description', 'Screen-printing white goods can be an untidy process and requires multiple screens. In addition to high rates of screen wear, the cost of consumables is a significant factor and long drying times prolong the production process. A laser marking machine is a cheaper alternative and can be used to provide an indelible mark quickly and easily. \r\n\r\nElectrox has designed a system that utilises two Raptor fibre laser markers. These lasers mark the whole panel in a single pass, have no consumables cost associated with them and also allow the panel to be moved on instantly to its'' next stage of manufacture.'),
(570, 1446, 'en', 'headline', 'Washing Machine Control Panel'),
(571, 1446, 'en', 'description', '<p>Electrox recommends the use of a Raptor fibre laser marker. This laser produces a large spot with mid-range energy density which produces high contrast graphical marks on the panels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To obtain further information on this application, please click on the case study below :-</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Laser-marked white goods are clearly better.</strong></p>\r\n'),
(572, 1446, 'en', 'metaTitle', 'White Goods Laser Marking Applications from Electrox'),
(573, 1446, 'en', 'metaDescription', 'Electrox manufactures laser marking equipment for the white goods industry.'),
