(579, 1447, 'en', 'marked', 'Spine Clamp'),
(580, 1447, 'en', 'process_description', 'Annealing or laser etching has largely replaced traditional chemical or mechanical methods for marking surgical implants. This change is largely explained by the greater accuracy and precision available with laser etching systems. \r\n\r\nUsing laser marking, It is possible to easily mark individual serial numbers and add company logos to products without the need to change tools or produce fresh masks.'),
(581, 1447, 'en', 'headline', 'Spine clamp'),
(582, 1447, 'en', 'description', '<p>The Electrox Scorpion Rapide II or Raptor fibre lasers are the recommended lasers for achieving a medum spot and mid-range energy density. These lasers can be used to produce high-contrast laser marks with mimimal material removal.</p>\r\n'),
