(612, 1450, 'en', 'marked', 'Surgical Instruments'),
(613, 1450, 'en', 'process_description', '"Tray management" was the accepted process for tracking and identifying surgical instruments for many years. But by using a Raptor or a Scorpion Rapide fibre laser marker it is possible to produce extremely small data matrix codes that contain the individual identity of each instrument. This therefore enables total traceability of instruments throughout both operating procedures and decontamination processes.'),
(614, 1450, 'en', 'headline', 'Medical Instruments'),
(615, 1450, 'en', 'description', '<p>A Scorpion Rapide or Raptor fibre laser marker is the best choice for marking medical instruments. These lasers can be used to deliver a medium-sized spot with a mid-range energy density which in turn produces a high contrast mark on the surgical steel with minimal material removal.&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
(616, 1450, 'en', 'metaTitle', 'Electrox Laser Marking Applications in the Medical Industry'),
(617, 1450, 'en', 'metaDescription', 'Electrox manufactures laser marking etching and engraving machines for the medical industry to mark metals, plastics and many other materials. '),
(618, 1450, 'en', 'video', ''),
(619, 1450, 'en', 'mark_type', 'Data matrix'),
(620, 1451, 'en', 'image', ''),
(621, 1451, 'en', 'status', 'Live'),
(622, 1451, 'en', 'material_description', 'High Speed Steel, Tool Steel or Carbide Steel'),
(623, 1451, 'en', 'marked', 'Milling Cutter'),
(624, 1451, 'en', 'process_description', 'Embossing, chemical etching or hand engraving have historically been used to mark metal cutting tools with identifying information such as diameters, serial numbers and/or manufacturing information. \r\n\r\nThe Electrox Scorpion Rapide and Raptor fibre laser markers produce a high contrast, dark annealed mark on HSS and Tool Steel and a high contrast, polished mark on Carbide. This clean and rapid technique can be used to mark individual serial numbers or logos without the need to change tools or produce fresh masks. '),
(625, 1451, 'en', 'headline', 'Milling Cutter'),
(626, 1451, 'en', 'description', '<p>For this application, we recommend using a Raptor or Scorpion Rapide fibre laser marker. These lasers&nbsp;can be used to produce a small spot size whilst the pulse width can be adjusted to vary the energy density required. By using the right combination it is possible&nbsp;to mark with a high contrast on to the high speed steel used in milling cutters.&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
(627, 1451, 'en', 'metaTitle', 'Electrox Laser Marking Applications In The Machine Tool Sector'),
(628, 1451, 'en', 'metaDescription', 'Electrox manufactures laser marking, etching and engraving equipment for use in the machine tooling sector to permanently mark machine milling and cutting tools and a range of other materials. '),
(629, 1451, 'en', 'video', ''),
(630, 1451, 'en', 'mark_type', 'Logos and serialised numbers.'),
(631, 1452, 'en', 'image', ''),
(632, 1452, 'en', 'status', 'Live'),
(633, 1452, 'en', 'material_description', 'Steel'),
(634, 1452, 'en', 'marked', 'Wood Cutter'),
(635, 1452, 'en', 'process_description', 'It is a legal requirement for all tool holders to be marked with their diameter, height and bore dimensions. The cutting blades within the holder are also individually identified (see illustration) for warranty purposes and authenticity. \r\n\r\nA Scorpion Rapide laser can be used to produce a high-contrast engraved mark through the anodised surface of the tool holder and a high-contrast polished surface mark on the cutter blade. '),
(636, 1452, 'en', 'headline', 'Wood Cutter'),
(637, 1452, 'en', 'description', '<p>The required capability for surface removal and deeper laser engraving is best provided by our Scorpion Rapide range of lasers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
